{'section_id': '8551ae91-339d-4c5a-9a35-f7e93770ee0d', 'section_data': {'metadata': {'id': '8551ae91-339d-4c5a-9a35-f7e93770ee0d', 'fullPath': '/project/workspace/preprocess.py', 'offset': 0, 'filename': 'preprocess.py', 'originalCode': 'import pandas as pd


def load_and_merge(mvp_path="data/mvp_votes.csv", stats_path="data/season_stats.csv"):
    mvp_df = pd.read_csv(mvp_path)
    stats_df = pd.read_csv(stats_path)

    # Normalize names
    mvp_df["Name"] = mvp_df["Name"].str.strip()
    stats_df["Player"] = stats_df["Player"].str.strip()

    # Merge on name + year
    merged = pd.merge(
        mvp_df,
        stats_df,
        left_on=["Name", "Year"],
        right_on=["Player", "Year"],
        how="left",
    )

    # Drop unnecessary columns
    drop_cols = ["Rk", "Player", "Pos", "Tm_y"]
    merged.drop(
        columns=[col for col in drop_cols if col in merged.columns], inplace=True
    )

    # Clean numeric columns
    for col in merged.columns:
        if merged[col].dtype == "object":
            try:
                merged[col] = merged[col].astype(float)
            except:
                pass

    # Assign ordinal MVP rank (1 = MVP)
    merged["Rank"] = merged.groupby("Year")["MVP_Points"].rank(
        ascending=False, method="first"
    )

    return merged


if __name__ == "__main__":
    df = load_and_merge()
    df.to_csv("data/merged_data.csv", index=False)
    print("Merged data saved to data/merged_data.csv")

{'section_id': '0f766e05-e7d6-402b-b278-18f44a379881', 'section_data': {'metadata': {'id': '0f766e05-e7d6-402b-b278-18f44a379881', 'fullPath': '/project/workspace/scraper.py', 'offset': 652, 'filename': 'scraper.py', 'originalCode': 'def scrape_season_stats(year):
    base_url_reg = (
        f"https://www.basketball-reference.com/leagues/NBA_{year}_per_game.html"
    )
    df_reg = pd.read_html(base_url_reg, header=0)[0]
    df_reg = df_reg[df_reg["Player"] != "Player"]  # remove repeated header rows
    df_reg["Year"] = year

    df_reg = df_reg[
        ["Player", "Year", "PTS", "AST", "TRB", "FG%"]
    ]  # Keep only specified columns
    df_reg = df_reg.dropna(
        subset=["PTS", "AST", "TRB", "FG%"]
    )  # Ensure key stats aren't invalid
    return df_reg

{'section_id': 'ec7067be-9150-416f-81be-6e3e4c6b5880', 'section_data': {'metadata': {'id': 'ec7067be-9150-416f-81be-6e3e4c6b5880', 'fullPath': '/project/workspace/rank_model.py', 'offset': 0, 'filename': 'rank_model.py', 'originalCode': 'import pandas as pd
from xgboost import XGBRanker
from sklearn.metrics import ndcg_score
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns


def load_data(path="data/merged_data.csv"):
    df = pd.read_csv(path)

    # Features to use
    feature_cols = [
        "PTS",
        "AST",
        "TRB",
        "FG%",
        "BPM",
        "WS/48",
        "TS%",
        "VORP",
        "WS",
        "PER",
    ]
    feature_cols = [
        col for col in feature_cols if col in df.columns
    ]  # only keep existing features
    df = df.dropna(subset=feature_cols + ["Rank"])

    # Sort by Year and Rank for consistency
    df = df.sort_values(by=["Year", "Rank"])

    X = df[feature_cols]
    y = df["Rank"]
    groups = df.groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    return X, y, groups, df


def evaluate_ndcg(y_true, y_pred, group_sizes):
    scores = []
    start = 0
    for size in group_sizes:
        true_ranks = y_true[start : start + size]
        true_relevance = (max(true_ranks) + 1) - true_ranks
        pred_scores = y_pred[start : start + size]
        scores.append(ndcg_score([true_relevance], [pred_scores]))
        start += size
    return np.mean(scores)


def plot_ranking_predictions(df, year):
    """
    Plot prediction error for a specific year.

    Args:
        df: DataFrame containing prediction results
        year: Year to plot prediction errors for
    """
    df["RankError"] = df["PredictedRank"] - df["Rank"]
    year_df = df[df["Year"] == year].copy()
    year_df.sort_values("Rank", inplace=True)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="Name", y="RankError", data=year_df, hue="Name", palette="coolwarm")
    plt.axhline(0, color="black", linestyle="--")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha="right")
    plt.ylabel("Predicted Rank - True Rank")
    plt.title(f"MVP Ranking Predictions ({year})")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(f"data/ranking_predictions_{year}.png")


def main():
    X, y, group, df = load_data()

    # Train-test split on years
    unique_years = df["Year"].unique()
    train_years, test_years = (
        unique_years[:-2],  # train: 2015-2023
        unique_years[-2:],  # test: 2024-2025
    )

    train_idx = df["Year"].isin(train_years)
    test_idx = df["Year"].isin(test_years)

    X_train, X_test = X[train_idx], X[test_idx]
    y_train, y_test = y[train_idx], y[test_idx]

    # Group sizes
    train_groups = df[train_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()
    test_groups = df[test_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    # Model
    model = XGBRanker(
        objective="rank:pairwise",
        learning_rate=0.1,
        n_estimators=100,
        max_depth=4,
        random_state=42,
    )

    print("Training XGBoostRanker...")
    model.fit(X_train, y_train, group=train_groups)

    # Predict, sort, and evaluate
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    df.loc[test_idx, "PredictedScore"] = y_pred
    df.loc[test_idx, "PredictedRank"] = (
        df.loc[test_idx]
        .groupby("Year")["PredictedScore"]
        .rank(ascending=False, method="first")
    )

    ndcg = evaluate_ndcg(y_test.to_numpy(), y_pred, test_groups)
    print(f"NDCG Score on test years {test_years.tolist()}: {ndcg:.4f}")

    # Show results
    print(df[test_idx][["Year", "Name", "Rank", "PredictedScore", "PredictedRank"]])
    plot_ranking_predictions(df, 2024)
    plot_ranking_predictions(df, 2025)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

def evaluate_ndcg(y_true, y_pred, group_sizes):

def plot_ranking_predictions(df, year):

        "FG%",
        "BPM",
        "WS/48",
        "TS%",
        "VORP",
        "WS",
        "PER",
    ]
    feature_cols = [
        col for col in feature_cols if col in df.columns
    ]  # only keep existing features
    df = df.dropna(subset=feature_cols + ["Rank"])

    # Sort by Year and Rank for consistency
    df = df.sort_values(by=["Year", "Rank"])

    X = df[feature_cols]
    y = df["Rank"]
    groups = df.groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    return X, y, groups, df


def evaluate_ndcg(y_true, y_pred, group_sizes):
    scores = []
    start = 0
    for size in group_sizes:
        true_ranks = y_true[start : start + size]
        true_relevance = (max(true_ranks) + 1) - true_ranks
        pred_scores = y_pred[start : start + size]
        scores.append(ndcg_score([true_relevance], [pred_scores]))
        start += size
    return np.mean(scores)


def plot_ranking_predictions(df, year):
    """
    Plot prediction error for a specific year.

    Args:
        df: DataFrame containing prediction results
        year: Year to plot prediction errors for
    """
    df["RankError"] = df["PredictedRank"] - df["Rank"]
    year_df = df[df["Year"] == year].copy()
    year_df.sort_values("Rank", inplace=True)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="Name", y="RankError", data=year_df, hue="PredictedRank", palette="coolwarm", dodge=True)
    plt.axhline(0, color="black", linestyle="--")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha="right")
    plt.ylabel("Predicted Rank - True Rank")
    plt.title(f"MVP Ranking Predictions ({year})")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(f"data/ranking_predictions_{year}.png")

def main():
    X, y, group, df = load_data()

    # Train-test split on years
    unique_years = df["Year"].unique()
    train_years, test_years = (
        unique_years[:-2],  # train: 2015-2023
        unique_years[-2:],  # test: 2024-2025
    )

    train_idx = df["Year"].isin(train_years)
    test_idx = df["Year"].isin(test_years)

    X_train, X_test = X[train_idx], X[test_idx]
    y_train, y_test = y[train_idx], y[test_idx]

    # Group sizes
    train_groups = df[train_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()
    test_groups = df[test_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    n_estimators_list = [100, 1000, 2000]
    ndcg_scores = {}

    for n_estimators in n_estimators_list:
        # Model
        model = XGBRanker(
            objective="rank:pairwise",
            learning_rate=0.1,
            n_estimators=n_estimators,
            max_depth=4,
            random_state=42,
        )

        print(f"\nTraining XGBoostRanker with n_estimators={n_estimators}...")
        model.fit(X_train, y_train, group=train_groups)

        # Predict, sort, and evaluate
        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        df.loc[test_idx, f"PredictedScore_{n_estimators}"] = y_pred
        df.loc[test_idx, f"PredictedRank_{n_estimators}"] = (
            df.loc[test_idx]
            .groupby("Year")[f"PredictedScore_{n_estimators}"]
            .rank(ascending=False, method="first")
        )

        ndcg = evaluate_ndcg(y_test.to_numpy(), y_pred, test_groups)
        ndcg_scores[n_estimators] = ndcg
        print(f"NDCG Score on test years {test_years.tolist()} (n_estimators={n_estimators}): {ndcg:.4f}")

        # Show results
        print(df[test_idx][["Year", "Name", "Rank", f"PredictedScore_{n_estimators}", f"PredictedRank_{n_estimators}"]])

    # Optionally, plot for the best n_estimators
    best_n = max(ndcg_scores, key=ndcg_scores.get)
    print(f"\nBest n_estimators based on NDCG: {best_n} (NDCG={ndcg_scores[best_n]:.4f})")
    # For plotting, copy the best predictions to 'PredictedRank' column
    df.loc[test_idx, "PredictedRank"] = df.loc[test_idx, f"PredictedRank_{best_n}"]
    plot_ranking_predictions(df, 2024)
    plot_ranking_predictions(df, 2025)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

{'section_data': {'lines': [22, 51], 'title': 'Untitled', 'summaryData': 'The scrape_season_stats function retrieves and processes both per-game and advanced NBA player statistics for a given year from Basketball Reference, cleans and filters the data to retain relevant columns and valid entries, and then merges the two datasets on player and year before returning the combined DataFrame.', 'createdAt': 1755993001000, 'metadata': {'fullPath': '/project/workspace/scraper.py', 'id': '12349374-3d5c-44e1-b765-430e45ec3b23', 'filename': 'scraper.py', 'offset': 652, 'originalCode': 'def scrape_season_stats(year):
    base_url_reg = (
        f"https://www.basketball-reference.com/leagues/NBA_{year}_per_game.html"
    )
    base_url_adv = (
        f"https://www.basketball-reference.com/leagues/NBA_{year}_advanced.html"
    )
    df_reg = pd.read_html(base_url_reg, header=0)[0]
    df_reg = df_reg[df_reg["Player"] != "Player"]  # remove repeated header rows
    df_reg["Year"] = year

    df_reg = df_reg[
        ["Player", "Year", "PTS", "AST", "TRB", "FG%"]
    ]  # Keep only specified columns
    df_reg = df_reg.dropna(
        subset=["PTS", "AST", "TRB", "FG%"]
    )  # Ensure key stats aren't invalid

    # Scrape advanced stats
    df_adv = pd.read_html(base_url_adv, header=0)[0]
    df_adv = df_adv[df_adv["Player"] != "Player"]  # remove repeated header rows
    df_adv["Year"] = year
    # Select a subset of advanced stats columns (modify as needed)
    adv_cols = ["Player", "Year", "PER", "TS%", "USG%", "WS", "BPM"]
    df_adv = df_adv[[col for col in adv_cols if col in df_adv.columns]]
    df_adv = df_adv.dropna(subset=[col for col in adv_cols if col in df_adv.columns and col not in ["Player", "Year"]])

    # Merge basic and advanced stats on Player and Year
    df_merged = pd.merge(df_reg, df_adv, on=["Player", "Year"], how="left")
    return df_merged'}, 'editPromptValue': ''}, 'section_id': '12349374-3d5c-44e1-b765-430e45ec3b23'}

{'section_data': {'lines': [1, 126], 'title': 'Untitled', 'summaryData': "This code loads basketball player data, trains an XGBoost ranking model to predict MVP rankings based on player statistics, evaluates the model's performance using NDCG, and visualizes prediction errors for specific years.", 'createdAt': 1755993188000, 'metadata': {'fullPath': '/project/workspace/rank_model.py', 'id': '6f77e874-9e3a-4cc1-a2e7-d54c43d876ab', 'filename': 'rank_model.py', 'offset': 0, 'originalCode': 'import pandas as pd
from xgboost import XGBRanker
from sklearn.metrics import ndcg_score
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns


def load_data(path="data/merged_data.csv"):
    df = pd.read_csv(path)

    # Features to use
    feature_cols = [
        "PTS",
        "AST",
        "TRB",
        "FG%",
        "BPM",
        "WS/48",
        "TS%",
        "VORP",
        "WS",
        "PER",
    ]
    feature_cols = [
        col for col in feature_cols if col in df.columns
    ]  # only keep existing features
    df = df.dropna(subset=feature_cols + ["Rank"])

    # Sort by Year and Rank for consistency
    df = df.sort_values(by=["Year", "Rank"])

    X = df[feature_cols]
    y = df["Rank"]
    groups = df.groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    return X, y, groups, df


def evaluate_ndcg(y_true, y_pred, group_sizes):
    scores = []
    start = 0
    for size in group_sizes:
        true_ranks = y_true[start : start + size]
        true_relevance = (max(true_ranks) + 1) - true_ranks
        pred_scores = y_pred[start : start + size]
        scores.append(ndcg_score([true_relevance], [pred_scores]))
        start += size
    return np.mean(scores)


def plot_ranking_predictions(df, year):
    """
    Plot prediction error for a specific year.

    Args:
        df: DataFrame containing prediction results
        year: Year to plot prediction errors for
    """
    df["RankError"] = df["PredictedRank"] - df["Rank"]
    year_df = df[df["Year"] == year].copy()
    year_df.sort_values("Rank", inplace=True)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="Name", y="RankError", data=year_df, hue="Name", palette="coolwarm")
    plt.axhline(0, color="black", linestyle="--")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha="right")
    plt.ylabel("Predicted Rank - True Rank")
    plt.title(f"MVP Ranking Predictions ({year})")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(f"data/ranking_predictions_{year}.png")


def main():
    X, y, group, df = load_data()

    # Train-test split on years
    unique_years = df["Year"].unique()
    train_years, test_years = (
        unique_years[:-2],  # train: 2015-2023
        unique_years[-2:],  # test: 2024-2025
    )

    train_idx = df["Year"].isin(train_years)
    test_idx = df["Year"].isin(test_years)

    X_train, X_test = X[train_idx], X[test_idx]
    y_train, y_test = y[train_idx], y[test_idx]

    # Group sizes
    train_groups = df[train_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()
    test_groups = df[test_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    # Model
    model = XGBRanker(
        objective="rank:pairwise",
        learning_rate=0.1,
        n_estimators=100,
        max_depth=4,
        random_state=42,
    )

    print("Training XGBoostRanker...")
    model.fit(X_train, y_train, group=train_groups)

    # Predict, sort, and evaluate
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    df.loc[test_idx, "PredictedScore"] = y_pred
    df.loc[test_idx, "PredictedRank"] = (
        df.loc[test_idx]
        .groupby("Year")["PredictedScore"]
        .rank(ascending=False, method="first")
    )

    ndcg = evaluate_ndcg(y_test.to_numpy(), y_pred, test_groups)
    print(f"NDCG Score on test years {test_years.tolist()}: {ndcg:.4f}")

    # Show results

{'section_id': '4d854851-8653-408f-8f6f-c60ce360376a', 'section_data': {'summaryData': 'The scrape_mvp_votes function retrieves NBA MVP voting data from Basketball Reference for each year in a specified range, extracts and renames relevant columns, and returns a combined DataFrame containing the year, player name, and MVP points for all years processed.', 'metadata': {'offset': 32, 'fullPath': '/project/workspace/scraper.py', 'id': '4d854851-8653-408f-8f6f-c60ce360376a', 'filename': 'scraper.py', 'originalCode': 'def scrape_mvp_votes(start_year=2018, end_year=2025):
    all_votes = []
    for year in range(start_year, end_year + 1):
        url = f"https://www.basketball-reference.com/awards/awards_{year}.html"
        tables = pd.read_html(url, header=1)
        try:
            mvp_table = tables[0]  # MVP table is the first table
            mvp_table["Year"] = year
            all_votes.append(mvp_table)
        except:
            print(f"Could not parse year {year}")

    df = pd.concat(all_votes)
    df = df.rename(columns={"Player": "Name", "Pts Won": "MVP_Points"})
    return df[["Year", "Name", "MVP_Points"]]'}, 'editPromptValue': '', 'title': 'Untitled', 'lines': [5, 19], 'createdAt': 1755968055000}}

{'section_id': 'dfec0dff-fac7-4bc2-b86d-71282e271b2c', 'section_data': {'summaryData': "This code loads basketball player data, trains an XGBoost ranking model to predict MVP rankings based on player statistics, evaluates the model's performance using NDCG, and visualizes prediction errors for recent years.", 'metadata': {'offset': 0, 'fullPath': '/project/workspace/rank_model.py', 'id': 'dfec0dff-fac7-4bc2-b86d-71282e271b2c', 'filename': 'rank_model.py', 'originalCode': 'import pandas as pd
from xgboost import XGBRanker
from sklearn.metrics import ndcg_score
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns


def load_data(path="data/merged_data.csv"):
    df = pd.read_csv(path)

    # Features to use
    feature_cols = [
        "PTS",
        "AST",
        "TRB",
        "FG%",
        "BPM",
        "WS/48",
        "TS%",
        "VORP",
        "WS",
        "PER",
    ]
    feature_cols = [
        col for col in feature_cols if col in df.columns
    ]  # only keep existing features
    df = df.dropna(subset=feature_cols + ["Rank"])

    # Sort by Year and Rank for consistency
    df = df.sort_values(by=["Year", "Rank"])

    X = df[feature_cols]
    y = df["Rank"]
    groups = df.groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    return X, y, groups, df


def evaluate_ndcg(y_true, y_pred, group_sizes):
    scores = []
    start = 0
    for size in group_sizes:
        true_ranks = y_true[start : start + size]
        true_relevance = (max(true_ranks) + 1) - true_ranks
        pred_scores = y_pred[start : start + size]
        scores.append(ndcg_score([true_relevance], [pred_scores]))
        start += size
    return np.mean(scores)


def plot_ranking_predictions(df, year):
    """
    Plot prediction error for a specific year.

    Args:
        df: DataFrame containing prediction results
        year: Year to plot prediction errors for
    """
    df["RankError"] = df["PredictedRank"] - df["Rank"]
    year_df = df[df["Year"] == year].copy()
    year_df.sort_values("Rank", inplace=True)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="Name", y="RankError", data=year_df, hue="Name", palette="coolwarm")
    plt.axhline(0, color="black", linestyle="--")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha="right")
    plt.ylabel("Predicted Rank - True Rank")
    plt.title(f"MVP Ranking Predictions ({year})")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(f"data/ranking_predictions_{year}.png")


def main():
    X, y, group, df = load_data()

    # Train-test split on years
    unique_years = df["Year"].unique()
    train_years, test_years = (
        unique_years[:-2],  # train: 2015-2023
        unique_years[-2:],  # test: 2024-2025
    )

    train_idx = df["Year"].isin(train_years)
    test_idx = df["Year"].isin(test_years)

    X_train, X_test = X[train_idx], X[test_idx]
    y_train, y_test = y[train_idx], y[test_idx]

    # Group sizes
    train_groups = df[train_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()
    test_groups = df[test_idx].groupby("Year").size().to_numpy()

    # Model
    model = XGBRanker(
        objective="rank:pairwise",
        learning_rate=0.1,
        n_estimators=100,
        max_depth=4,
        random_state=42,
    )

    print("Training XGBoostRanker...")
    model.fit(X_train, y_train, group=train_groups)

    # Predict, sort, and evaluate
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    df.loc[test_idx, "PredictedScore"] = y_pred
    df.loc[test_idx, "PredictedRank"] = (
        df.loc[test_idx]
        .groupby("Year")["PredictedScore"]
        .rank(ascending=False, method="first")
    )

    ndcg = evaluate_ndcg(y_test.to_numpy(), y_pred, test_groups)
    print(f"NDCG Score on test years {test_years.tolist()}: {ndcg:.4f}")

    # Show results
    print(df[test_idx][["Year", "Name", "Rank", "PredictedScore", "PredictedRank"]])
    plot_ranking_predictions(df, 2024)
    plot_ranking_predictions(df, 2025)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
